cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with unsupervised learning and inference from noisy data, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning and artificial intelligence communities. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are likely sub-categories. The paper also involves modeling and estimation of probability distributions, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). The concept of multiple copies of data and their use in determining the true distribution is related to the field of data science, which is covered by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper introduces a new approach called 'dependent component analysis', which could be considered a sub-field of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
